label.value: advanced trauma care for nurses certificate

definition.value: An information content entity that is a specific output of a person participating in an advanced trauma care for nurses program and that certifies successful completion of the program.

label.value: trauma nursing core course plan specification

definition.value: A plan specification that specifies the content, methodology, evaluation of a course aimed at nurses and providing cognitive knowledge and psychomotoric skills that help optimizing trauma patient care in a hospital setting.

label.value: trauma nursing core course certificate

definition.value: An information content entity that is a specified output of a person participating in an trauma nursing core course and that certifies successful completion of that course.

label.value: employment contract document act

definition.value: A deontic document act that creates a mutally dependent employee and employer role.
JPB (20 March 2017): should output employee role and employer role

label.value: racial category information

definition.value: An information content identity that describes a social categorization of human beings by assumptions based on physical characteristics or their assumed lineage

label.value: abbreviated injury scale training course plan specification

definition.value: A plan specification that specifies the content, methodology, and evaluation of a training course teaching the Abbreviated Injury Scale (AIS), informs about coding rules and conventions, and discusses methods for assessing the multiple injury patient.

label.value: abbreviated injury scale training course

definition.value: A planned process that realizes the concretization of an abbreviated injury scale training course plan specification.

label.value: collection of general surgeons with ATLS training

definition.value: A collection of general surgeons that has successfully completed the advanced life support course.

Initially, we used the SubClass restriction, with 'only'  after 'is aggregate of' as an equivalent to restriction, which fully defines this set. label.value: general surgeon role

definition.value: A physician role borne by a human being and that, if realized, is being realized by its bearer using operative manual and instrumental techniques on a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas without the bearer of the role specializing into any particular field of surgery.

label.value: collection of general surgeons current in ATLS

definition.value: A collection of general surgeons with ATLS training for which the training has not been more than the time specified before their knowledge is no longer deemed current.

label.value: general surgery privileges role

label.value: trauma program internal practice-based learning course certificate

definition.value: An information content entity that is a specific output of a person participating in an internal trauma program course using a practice based learning approach and that certifies successful completion of the course.

label.value: practice-based learning trauma care course plan specification

definition.value: A practice-based learning course plan specification that aims to improve the quality of patient outcomes in trauma medicine.

label.value: collection of trauma surgeons on a trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists exclusively of trauma surgeons that are listed on the trauma on call plan specification.

This class already follows the strategy of not fully defining collections (using universal restrictions) due to the reasoning load it creates. We only represent which properties the affirmed members of this class have using a necessary existential restriction

label.value: obsolete_on call exclusivity obligee role

definition.value: An obligee role that inheres in a human being mentioned in an on call plan specification and that, if realized, is realized by its bearer participating a planned process realizing the concretization of the plan specification and being on call exclusively for the organization at specified times that is the contractual partner in the document act that created this role.

label.value: collection of trauma surgeons with on call exclusivity

definition.value: A collection of trauma surgeons who are members of the trauma service of an organization and are exclusively on call for that organization.

label.value: critical care certificate course plan specfication

definition.value: A plan specification that specifies the content, methodology, evaluation of a course to relay information and exercise procedures relevant to optimize critical care.

label.value: critical care certificate course

definition.value: A planned process that is the realization of the concretization of a critical care certificate course plan specification.

label.value: critical care certificate

definition.value: An information content entity that is the specified output of a critical care certificate course.

label.value: collection of trauma surgeons certified for critical care

definition.value: A collection of trauma surgeons that are part of the on call list of an organization and are certified in critical care.

label.value: trauma surgery fellowship program

definition.value: A medical fellowship that provides education in using operative manual or instrumental techniques on a patient to investigate or treat an injury or other pathological situation that are caused by an injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.

label.value: successful completion of trauma surgery fellowship information content entity

definition.value: An information content entity that is the specified output of a person successfully fulfilling the evaluation criteria at the end of a a trauma-focused post-residency training that lasts a minimum of one year and provides additional knowledge and experience in the management of injured patients.

label.value: obsolete_collection of fellowship-trained trauma surgeons on a trauma panel

definition.value: A collection of trauma surgeons that are part of the on call list of an organization and for whom exists information about successfully finishing a trauma surgery fellowship program.

label.value: collection of orthopedic surgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a trauma surgeon role an that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification.

label.value: collection of orthopedic surgeons on trauma service fulfilling CME requirement

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a orthopedic surgeon role an that are mentioned in the trauma panel and that particpates in trauma education verifiable for 18 hours over 3 years.

label.value: board eligible orthopedic surgeon role

definition.value: An orthopedic surgeon role that is the outcome of fullfilling all obligations to be allowed to take a board certification exam in orthopedic surgery.

label.value: board certified orthopedic surgeon role

definition.value: An orthopedic surgeon role that is the specified output of a board certification process and that, if realized, is realized by its bearer using operative manual or instrumental techniques on the musculoskeletal system of a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.

label.value: collection of board eligible orthopedic surgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of orthopedic surgeons mentioned on the trauma on call plan specification that fulfil all criteria to sit a board certification exam, but that either have not taken one or have failed.

label.value: collection of board certified orthopedic surgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of orthopedic surgeons that are mentioned in the trauma on call plan specification and that are board certified in orthopedic surgery.

label.value: general orthopedic surgery privileges role

definition.value: A deontic role that is the specified outcome of a document act between the head of a orthopedic surgery and the bearer of a orthopedic surgeon role that, of realized, is realized by its bearer admitting, evaluating, diagnosing, consulting, and providing pre-, intra and post-operative care, and performing orthopedic surgical procedures, to patients of all ages, to correct or treat various conditions, diseases, disorders, and injuries of the musculoskeletal system.

label.value: obsolete_collection of orthopedic surgeons on trauma panel with general orthopedic surgery privileges

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a orthopedic surgeon role that are mentioned in the trauma on call plan specification and that are also bearing a general orthopedic surgery privileges role.

label.value: hospital neurological injury triage plan specification

definition.value: A plan specification that specifies under which circumstances and with which neurological injuries patients admitted to one hospital will be triaged to another healthcare provider organization when no neurosurgical coverage is available at the first hospital.

label.value: TMD-approved hospital neurological injury triage plan specification

definition.value: A plan specification that specifies under which circumstances and with which neurological injuries patients will be triaged from the emergency department to another healthcare provider organization when limited or no neurosurgical coverage is available and that is the specified output of an approval process through the trauma medical director.

label.value: collection of neurosurgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a neurosurgeon role that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification.

label.value: collection of orthopedic surgeons with on call exclusivity

definition.value: A collection of orthopedic surgeons who are members of the trauma service of an organization and are exclusively on call for that organization.

label.value: collection of neurosurgeons with on call exclusivity

definition.value: A collection of neurosurgeons that are members of the trauma service of an organization and are exclusively on call for that organization.

label.value: collection of neurosurgeons on trauma service fulfilling CME requirement

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a neurosurgeon role that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification and that particpates in trauma education verifiable for 18 hours over 3 years.

label.value: collection of anesthesiologists on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of an anesthesiologist role that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification.

label.value: anesthesiology residency program

definition.value: A medical residency in the medical speciality that focuses on the administration of medication for the temporary general or local suppression of sensory or motor nerve function during some health care encounter or on making decisions regarding the administration of such medication.

label.value: successful completion of anesthesiology residency information content entity

definition.value: An information content entity that is the specified output of a person successfully fulfilling the evaluation criteria at the end of an anesthesiology residency program.

label.value: collection of anesthesiologists with anesthesiology residency on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of an anesthesiologist role and that have successfully completed an anesthesiology residency and that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification.

label.value: advanced practice registered nurse role

definition.value: A nurse role that is the specified output of post-graduate education in nursing and that is realized by using extended and expanded skills, experience and knowledge in assessment, planning, implementation, diagnosis and evaluation of the care required.

label.value: certified registered nurse anesthetist role

definition.value: An advanced practice registered nurse role that is the specified outcome of an accredition process with the Council of Accreditation in the United States of American and depends on graduate level education and board certification in anesthesiology.

label.value: collection of certified registered nurse anesthetist

definition.value: A collection of humans that only has bearers of an certified registered nurse anesthetist role as members.
